  "title": "TestCaseFail",
  "source": "chm_extract_v15/CANoeCANalyzer/Topics/CAPLFunctions/Test/Functions/CAPLfunctionTestCaseFail.htm",
  "syntax": [
    "TestCaseFail ();"
  ],
  "description": [
    "You can set the verdict of the current test case to fail. This function can only be used within a test case. It is not possible to set the verdict of this test case back to pass."
  ],
  "parameters": [],
  "return": "—",
  "example": {
    "description": [],
    "code": "// checks if the value of the signal is in the given range\ntestcase CheckSignalValue()\n{\n   long result;\n   result = checkSignalInRange(Node_SUT::Velocity, 60, 100);\n   if (result != 1)\n   TestCaseFail();\n}"
  },
